Why does it have to end up like that, my mom totally understand why im not playing football, my heart isnt in it anymore, its not!I just wanna scream, i do, my dad and kelly sit there and tell me how varsity football is good in my life, yes i know, yes i might regret it, but ITS what i want to do, my dad tells me how much HE was looking forward to have me and alex play varsity football, he told me it breaks HIS heart that im not playing, it doesnt break mine, yes i know i will learn my lesson, but life is all about descisions and i have made one that will change my life, everyone sits here and tells me im good and asks why i dont want to play, i dont want to, and i love kelly and my dad too death but sometimes i just want to scream, i told kelly maybe im not dedicated enough to play football this year, but she said dedication is a good thing to have and varsity football would teach u it, im qutting football so i can be DEDICATED to baseball all-year round, i know im not the best,but im gonna work untill im up there, i need to work on the little things before i can be better  .This summer hasnt been what i thought it would be, its nothing...yes ive had my fun, my ups but ive had my downs, i didnt start the summer off good, thinkin i would spend it with the girl i loved,but that just blew up in my face, i have gotton closer to alot of people and i have drifted away from some,what i thought it was gonna be was a complete 360, yes i have partied alot,i should have told people stuff i told myself i would tell them,but im not going to regret any of it, i quit football so i can move on with my life, im almost 16...im going to get a job and worry about that...i have achieved one of my high school goals and that is getting my varsity letter, i have gotten that, now i am going to achieve higher things....i needed to get that out of me..bye
